### Section B — The Compulsory Question Pattern
25 compulsory questions identified: B14, B16, B18, B21, B26, B32, B35, B38, B42, B50, B52, B55, B58, B61, B65, B67, B69, B73, B78, B80, B83, B86, B89, B93, B95.

**The compulsory B question (always Q11 in the exam) tests ethics and the CISI Code of Conduct in every sitting. This is guaranteed marks if you know the Code.** See @knowledge-base/topics/risk-in-financial-services/ethics-integrity-cisi-code.md.

### Section C — Recurring Essay Themes
- Regulatory reform (Brexit, Edinburgh Reforms, FSMA 2023)
- ESG / sustainability / climate risk
- Fintech / cryptoassets
- Conduct risk / culture
- Market abuse enforcement
- SM&CR and corporate governance

