## Workbook Cross-References

These chapters reference each other extensively:
- Ch1 ↔ Ch2: regulatory structure ↔ FCA objectives and supervision
- Ch1 ↔ Ch3: FSMA Part VIII ↔ market abuse and insider dealing
- Ch2 ↔ Ch3: SYSC 18 ↔ whistleblowing provisions
- Ch2 ↔ Ch5: SM&CR ↔ SM&CR review / regulatory reform
- Ch2 ↔ Ch6: compliance function (SYSC 6) ↔ BIS 10 principles and ethics

## High-ROI Study Targets

If you only have limited time, study these topics first (highest frequency + highest exam weight):

1. **CISI Code of Conduct** (Ch6, 15%) — tested in EVERY compulsory B question
2. **SM&CR** (Ch2, 40%) — prescribed responsibilities, certification, conduct rules
3. **FSMA general prohibition and regulated activities** (Ch1, 20%) — 52 Section A questions
4. **PRIN / Principles for Businesses** (Ch2, 40%) — including Consumer Duty (Principle 12)
5. **SYSC systems and controls** (Ch2, 40%) — compliance function, conflicts, outsourcing
6. **Market abuse / insider dealing** (Ch3, 20%) — MAR, CJA 1993, defences
7. **Financial promotions** (Ch2, 40%) — s21, COBS 4, social media, cryptoassets
8. **Client categorisation and suitability** (Ch2, 40%) — COBS 3, 9/9A
9. **Money laundering / POCA / MLR** (Ch3, 20%) — three stages, SARs, JMLSG
10. **Enforcement / DEPP** (Ch2, 40%) — RDC, notices, penalties framework
11. **BIS 10 compliance principles** (Ch6, 15%) — board and management responsibilities
12. **Complaints / FOS / FSCS** (Ch2, 40%) — procedures, timings, compensation limits
13. **Takeover Code general principles** (Ch3, 20%) — six principles, mandatory offer
14. **Bribery Act** (Ch3, 20%) — s7 corporate liability, adequate procedures
15. **Conflicts of interest** (Ch2, 40%) — SYSC 10, information barriers
